Papa, when I was six years old I could stand on my head; but now I have lost the art, alas!
â
âNow, Alice, do try to be sensible, if you ever had such an opening.
You know that I do not very often act rashly; but you will make me think I have done so now, unless you behave most steadily.
â
âPapa, I am steadiness itself; but you must make allowance for a little upset at the marvels heaped upon me.
â
âMy dear child, there are no marvels; or, at any rate, none for you to know.
