His features, too, were clear and bold, and his jaws just obstinate enough to manage a parish; without that heavy squareness which sets church and parish by the ears.
The Grower was of moderate height, and sturdy, and thoroughly useful; his face told of many dealings with the world; but his eyes were frank, and his mouth was pleasant.
His custom was to let other people have their say before he spoke; and now he saluted Mr. Hales in silence, and waited for him to begin.
âI hope,â said his visitor, âyou will excuse my freedom in coming to see you thus.
