âI shall stop it all, when I please,â he said to himself, every night at bed-time; âlet them have their little game, and make up their minds to astonish me.
â For he, like almost every man who has attained the age of sixty, looked back upon love as a brief excrescence, of about as much importance as a wart.
âAy, ay, no need to tell me,â he answered, when Mrs. Lovejoy, under the parsonâs advice, and at Mabelâs entreaty, broke the matter to him.
âI donât go about with my eyes shut, wife.
