âOne acre is as good as another to a man of modern lineage.
Some of that land passed from us at the time of the great confiscation, and some was sold by that reckless man, the last Sir Hilary but one.
The Chapmans have held very little of it for even so much as two centuries; how then can they be attached to it?
No, no.
