Now, mind, she will pay a deal of heed to you now that you are a full-blown counsellor: young Jenkins is the man, remember; no more about that young dashing Lorraine.
â
âNo, father, no more about him,â said Gregory, sadly and submissively.
âI wish I had never brought him here.
â
âNo harm, my son; no harm whatever.
That little fancy must be quite worn out.
Elias is not over bright, as we know; but he is a steady and worthy young fellow, and will make her a capital husband.
â
âWell, that is the main point after all--a steadfast man who will stick to her.
