â He spoke like a fool, confounding coarsely her essence and her instincts.
And perhaps some little turn of contrast broke the seals of anguish.
She looked up, and she smiled, to show her proper sense of duty; and then (without knowledge of what she did) she pressed her right hand to her heart, and leaned on a rail, and fell forward into a torrent of shameless weeping.
She was as a little child once more, whose soul is overwhelmed with woe.
And all along the hollow hedges went the voice of sobbing.
