How do you mean to settle it?
â
âI think you should rather tell me, Martin, how you mean to settle it.
She might have been settled long ago, in a good position and comfortable, if my advice had been heeded.
But you are the most obstinate man in the world.
â
âWell, well, my dear, I donât think that you should be hard upon any one in that respect.
