And even in his time, this strange river was legendary as the Hydaspes.
After the heavy and tempestuous rain, the night was fair, as it generally is, even in the worst of weather, when the full moon rises.
The long-chained hill, with its level outline stretching towards the south of east, afforded play for the glancing light of a watery and laborious moon.
