â
âBless the boyâs tongue, and yours too!
â cried the Rector.
âI should not care twopence about his tongue, if he only used his teeth properly.
â
âAh, Struan, Struan!
those who have never known what ache or pain is, cannot hope to understand the system.
I know exactly how to treat him--a course of gentle drastics first, and then three days of my electuary, and then cardamomum, exhibited with liquor potassy.
