â
In confirmation of this opinion, a tall grey form, with one arm thrown up, and a long cloak hanging gracefully, came suddenly gliding between the trees.
The maiden, whose brain had been overwrought, tried to spring up with her usual vigour; but her power failed her.
She fell back against the sepulchral trunk and did not faint, but seemed for the moment very much disposed thereto.
When she was perfectly sure of herself, and rid of all presence of spectres, she found a strong arm behind her head, and somebody leaning over her.
And she laid both hands before her face, without meaning any rudeness; having never been used to be handled at all, except by her brother or father.
âI beg your pardon most humbly, madam.
