Of course he was carried down stream as he did it; but slowly (compared with a floating body).
And he found that the movement was much less rapid, at three or four feet from the surface.
Before he had time to think of this, or fairly fetch his balance, the white thing he was waiting for came gliding in the blackness towards him.
